olive oil
2 potato
1 tomato
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries. Thinly slice tomato into rounds.

• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle generously with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Spread out evenly and bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, the egg and Aussie spice blend in a large bowl, then season with pepper.
• Using damp hands, shape beef mixture into 2cm-thick patties (1 per person).

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the ingredients and shaping the mixture into patties!

• Pat haloumi dry and slice in half crossways to get 1 thin piece per person.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base. Cook haloumi until golden brown, 2 minutes each side. Set aside on a paper towel-lined plate.
• Return frying to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side.
• In the last 1-2 minutes of cook time, sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over patties and cover with a lid so cheese melts.



• While the patties are cooking, halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.

• Spread mayonnaise over burger bun bases. Top with some mixed salad leaves, a cheesy beef patty, haloumi, some onion chutney and tomato.
• Serve with fries. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the burgers!